  div(class="blurb", id="Schāpd-basics")
    div(class="container")
      div(class="row")
        div(class="col-md-12")
          h2 Project Description
        div(class="col-sm-6")
          h4 What is Schāpd? 
          p  Schāpd /SHāpd/ is a simple, browser based graphic designing program 
           | based around the idea that everything can be illustrated with shapes.
           | Unlike other methods of "shape" drawing, Schāpd aims to foster an entirely
           | different approach to illustration by not simply including shape as vauge
           | form, but using shape to convey details, depth, and space.
          br

          h4 Schāpd Basics
          p The Schāpd web application allows users (or Artists as Schāpd refers to them as)
           | to create an account using their Facebook credentials.  For illustration, 
           | Schāpd provides artists with two shape types: a circle and a triangle.  Artists
           | can create more shapes by using the different three shape interaction functions:
           | joining, subtracting, and dividing.  With these simple tools, any shape can be 
           | manufactured.  The Artist's account is able to retrieve previously stored shapes, 
           | and, in that spirit, the artist can save shapes to his or her account.
        div(class="col-sm-6")
          img(src='images/logo.png', height="350", width="350")

