  div(class="blurb", id="Schāpd-influences")
    div(class="container")
      div(class="row")
        div(class="col-md-12")
          h2 Project Justification
        div(class="col-md-8")
          img(src='images/abstract.png', width='600', height='540', id='abst')
        div(class="col-md-4")
          h4 Schāpd and Me
          ul
            li ART260: Computer Graphics
            li ART350: Visual Thinking
            li CMSI371: Computer Graphics
            li CMSI401: Software Engineering Laboratory
            li CMSI486: Database Structures 
          
          h4 Schāpd Trinity
          ol
            li Everyone is creative.
            li Creation should be free.
            li Simplicity is everything.
          p Everyone is born creative, with a great capacity for great design. 
            | Over the years, however, this creativity is smothered by institutions 
            | that praise only those who can conceive the lifelike in line art. 
            | Schāpd hopes to remove this silly notion that line is the only way to design. 
            | Schāpd aims to remove those preconceived notions about artists and those who 
            | appreciate art. Because everyone can be an artist, no sweeping generalizations 
            | behind what an "artist" wears or how an "artist" behaves. With Schāpd, creation 
            | is now free and open to everyone.

  div(class="blurb", id="Schāpd-itself")
    div(class="container")
      div(class="row")
        div(class="col-md-12")
          h2 Schāpd Interface
        div(class="col-md-7")
          br
          img(src='images/canvas.png', height="250", width="500")
          br
          img(src='images/shapes.png', height="336", width="500")
        div(class="col-xs-4")
          h4 Drawing Functions
          dl
            dt Triangle
              dd A polygon with 3 sides and 3 vertices.
            dt Circle
              dd The shape defined by a collection of points that are equidistant from 
                | one single point.
            dt Joining
              dd Once two shapes are selected, the shapes will be joined to form one large shape.
            dt Subtracting
              dd Once two shapes are selected, the shape selected first will be 
                | subtracted from the shape selected second, or rather, a negative 
                | area will appear in the second shape where the first shape used to be.
            dt Dividing
              dd Once two shapes are selected, the shapes will be divided into three shapes,
                | the two original shapes will have negative areas where they overlapped and
                | a third shape where the overlap was.
        div(class="col-xs-1")
          img(src='images/toolbar.png', height="500", width="61", class='logo-img')

  div(class="blurb", id="Schāpd-Challenges")
    div(class="container")
